The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 16 December is 126,678 (14,600.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 11 December, there were 5,337 new confirmed cases (615.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 04 December, there were 5,891 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 9% (554 fewer cases).
